{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6858025f-23d0-4b7d-abac-82553645d07f","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n// Change SDK version to\n\"version\": \"11.0.100\"\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Change base images\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"937e8fa9-83c7-403c-b8d8-2f1951369a19","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to explore any codebase since they're describing their setup. Let me provide concise instructions.","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"C42E:691FE:1DBEBCA:219566B:6A07C937"},"id":"6c7f39d7-d2db-4471-8a8d-eab9c118d85f","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:32:46.017Z","parentId":"5d0610fd-c5d6-425e-a245-5a63bcf0e102"}
